<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Juna</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-16 16:26:54</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>HA HA! 5K??? You are absolutely out of your mind. For 5K you can get a Ykesha procing weapon. The rings sell across the four servers I play on for 300pp and under. As far as the Fishbone goes, it is worth far more than the GSB. The High Shaman in Sol A is harder to get to, but spawns 3 times as much and relatively few classes need the ring to begin with. My monk got one for free just being in the room at the right time.<BR>
<BR>
5K for a Glowing Stone Band?, and someone else thinking twice about trading it for a FBE? Thanks for the laughs, and Oh, tell me what servers you are on. If this is the summation of your EQ economy/item knowledge, I have a bridge in SK I think you'd be interested in.<BR>
<BR>
By the way, maximumeq is a good site for item info, but many items are falsely priced (such as the ~600 it says the GSB goes for). It only takes a few fake inputs by someone wanting to change the price to do so. There is no e-mail or true character identification here. For REAL prices, you are better off on a dedicated server board, or a really large and frequently updated board, such as the Druid Grove.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Thanks for the laugh.</font></td></tr></table>
